# Cyrius has no nested JSON value type, so id/params/result/data are
# carried as raw JSON-literal C strings ("1", "\"abc\"", "null", "{...}").
# A 0 sentinel for `id` means "not present" (notification).

# JsonRpcRequest (32 bytes):
#   +0  jsonrpc  cstr ("2.0")
#   +8  id       cstr or 0 (0 = notification)
#   +16 method   cstr
#   +24 params   cstr or 0 (raw JSON literal, defaults to "null")

